				\begin{document}$$\pm logFC\cdot -\,log(Pval)$$\end{document}±logFC⋅−log(Pval), resulting in ordered gene lists having the most up regulated genes on the top and the most down regulated genes in the bottom. The Kendall Tau Distance40 was then used to evaluate the similarity between ENMs, drugs and ENMs-drugs based on the ranked lists of genes. The Kendall Tau distance between two lists T1 and T2 is defined as follow:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
